{/* CHALLENGES SECTION                                                  */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "challenges" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <p class="mb-4">
    Goat Funded Trader offers a broad range of challenge types — <strong>1-Step</strong>, <strong>2-Step</strong> (GOAT, Standard, and PRO variants), <strong>3-Step</strong>, <strong>Instant</strong> (GOAT and Standard), <strong>Goat Blitz</strong>, and <strong>Pay Later</strong> — with no time limits on evaluations. Each model has different pricing, drawdown rules, and payout structures.
  </p>

  <!-- Challenge summary cards -->
  <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">One-Step Challenge</p>
      <p>Requires a 10% profit target with a 4% daily drawdown and 6% max drawdown. Fastest route to funding with the strictest limits. Account sizes from $15K to $200K ($138–$798).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Two-Step Challenge (GOAT, Standard &amp; PRO)</p>
      <p>Split evaluation into two stages. GOAT variant has lower targets (8%/6%) with 4% daily DD and 10% max DD. Standard requires 10%/5% with 5% daily DD and 10% max DD. PRO variant also available. Account sizes from $5K to $200K ($22–$730).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Three-Step Challenge</p>
      <p>Three phases each requiring 6% profit target with 4% daily drawdown and 8% max drawdown. Account sizes from $10K to $200K ($48–$498). Best for conservative, steady traders.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Instant Funding (GOAT &amp; Standard)</p>
      <p>Skip the evaluation entirely. GOAT variant: 3% trailing daily DD, 6% trailing max DD. Standard variant: 4% daily DD, 8% max DD. Higher fees and stricter rules. GOAT from $5K–$100K ($107–$767), Standard from $2.5K–$50K ($73–$1,434).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Goat Blitz &amp; Pay Later</p>
      <p>Additional model options. Goat Blitz offers a fast-track evaluation route. Pay Later lets traders start a challenge and defer the fee. Check the GFT website for current terms on these models.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

